While working on this project, what surprised me the most was how easily people fall into cyber traps without realizing it.
Many attacks, like phishing or UPI fraud, do not require advanced hacking skills—just simple tricks and human mistakes. 
I realized that lack of awareness is the biggest weakness, not technology.
One habit I will definitely change is being more careful before clicking on links or sharing personal information online.
Earlier, I used to trust messages or emails quickly, but now I will verify sources and think twice before taking any action.
This project made me understand that staying alert and informed is the best way to stay safe in the digital world.
